div.div: I personally love this idea. Few comments on perfect freehand: The dots, ie clicking sometimes get cut off (see video below) Other then that, really cool! Would love to see this in excalidraw.

Oh by the way, I'm happy to help work on this. I've personally used https://next-auth.js.org/ but since excalidraw doesn't use next (and I'm sure it is compatible) it won't work. If you can let me know how I can help, that'd be great!
Commented on #3498 Suggestion: GitHub bot to auto update and render files

Yes, that covers everything I imagine. I think there needs to be a way to import from a hosted provider to make changes. Ie, import from github then provide a repo URL with a branch and path to the file, you can then authenticate with github, and if you have perms to commit on the repo, commit on the repo, if not, fork, make new branch, and create a pr.
